# AES-256-GCM NIST CAVS Reference Vector Spec
#
# Tests the existing aes256_gcm_encrypt / aes256_gcm_decrypt implementation
# against authoritative NIST CAVS test vectors (gcmEncryptExtIV256.rsp) as
# published through the RustCrypto AEADs project and the NIST Cryptographic
# Algorithm Validation Program (CAVP).
#
# NOTE: src/os/crypto/aes_gcm.spl implements AES-256-GCM only (32-byte keys).
#       NIST SP 800-38D Appendix B test cases B.1–B.4 use 16-byte (AES-128)
#       keys and are therefore not applicable here.  The vectors below are all
#       from gcmEncryptExtIV256.rsp (32-byte key, 12-byte IV, 16-byte tag).
#
# Purpose: green baseline for future SIMD / optimisation passes. A regression
#          means the optimisation changed crypto semantics.
#
# Source: https://github.com/RustCrypto/AEADs/blob/master/aes-gcm/tests/aes256gcm.rs
#         (cites NIST CAVP gcmEncryptExtIV256.rsp)

use os.crypto.aes_gcm.{aes256_gcm_encrypt, aes256_gcm_decrypt, AesGcmResult}

# ============================================================================
# Vector helpers — built at module level to avoid it-block var-mutation footgun
# (see memory: feedback_it_block_var_mutation.md)
# ============================================================================

# --- Vector V1: empty plaintext, empty AAD ---
